        "text": "Review the ThreadMode work at Weblogs and Wikis [http://erhetoric.org/WeblogsAndWikis/wikka.php?wakka=HomePage traditional wiki]. You'll see that not a lot of thread mode discussion comes to much, in great part because adding to thread mode becomes a way of avoiding committing to creating a dissertation page.  Students report every semester, \"Doing ThreadMode is just easier!\" The addition to a thread might help the writer think about an idea - but, I'd suggest, so does taking energy to start a dissertation page. Yes, adding to a thread might spur the next person into action, get her thinking about a new idea- but so can a dissertation page."
