        "text": "ThreadMode was not intended to be the record of an exchange but a technique of invention. The idea was akin to the brainstorm, with a dose of exploring for stasis and topical arguments. The idea was to collectively voice multiple arguments - not necessarily in support of one's own but to add to the pool of arguments and perspectives that need to be considered. The idea is that once a page - a dissertation - starts to gel, we then have a place to establish stubs, which lead to other perspectives, ideologies, compositions. The vision of the wiki as a collaborative document and workspace comes forward when we can constellate these various dissertations. Rather than embedding a set of possible ideas and arguments in a single page along a thread, we create webs with documents. "
