      "item": {
        "type": "html",
        "id": "ab267c8cb10f5bcf",
        "text": "<b>ThreadMode emphasizes practices of conversation rather than invention</b> TheadMode is taken as an invitation to discussion rather than as an invitation to invention, and threads tend to show the usual patterns of discussions online - patterns that get in the way of developing invention. For instance, One-Person - One-Perspective tends to be foregrounded in threads. This is especially pronounced in students working on the wiki in that they understand their way of thinking as theirs and theirs alone and proclaim that Every Person Has A Different Opinion. The belief gets in the way of seeing patterns in the arguments, and we need patterns to get to DiscourseMode."
      },
