        "text": "Participants tended to view ThreadMode as a kind of [[Speaker's Corner]]. We envisioned lots of discussion, leading to a developing document. But the ThreadMode became a loose collection of soapboxes, each speaker addressing a different public. A set of monologues rather than speakers in dialogue. This arrangement can work, but it needs a moderator to synthesize the ideas. Hard work. The moderator has to be both intrusive - not afraid of re-working specific statements - and external to the argument in order to be, um, moderate. Few want the position."
